<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">W is one of the trickiest tiles in Scrabble. Most players only think of WA-, WE-, WI-, WO- combinations — but dozens of valid words feature W followed by a consonant. These unusual patterns are your secret weapon when the board doesn't offer a vowel slot next to your W placement.</p>

